items.title: Error while trying to connect local git repository to another remote git repository
items.body:
As per https://github.com/chrisparnin/EngineeringBasics/blob/master/Git.md#git, I was practicing to create a Repo. I created a local git repository from command line and created a README.md within it.

Now to connect the local repo with a remote one, I followed the instructions on GitHub to add a remote URL to an existing git repository:

git remote add origin https://github.ncsu.edu/alokann/Project.git

git push -u origin master

But I got the following error:

error: src refspec master does not match any.

error: failed to push some refs to 'https://github.ncsu.edu/alokann/Project.git'

Does anyone have an idea, what might be the issue?

items.title: Error in listBranches(owner,repo)
items.body:
This question is regarding the REST API workshop that happened on 4th September.

I managed to finish the 1st function listRepos() and am trying to work on the second listBranches(owner,repo).

But I am receiving this response from the API, any idea how to solve it. 

{
  message: 'Must authenticate to access this API.',
  documentation_url: 'https://developer.github.com/enterprise/2.18/v3'
}

I authenticated myself via the two commands recommended on the given site, but still facing the same problem. Any solution?
